.TH "phy_set_asym_pause" 9 "phy_set_asym_pause" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phy_set_asym_pause \- Configure Pause and Asym Pause
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" phy_set_asym_pause
.BI "(struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "bool rx "  ","
.BI "bool tx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phydev" 12
target phy_device struct
.IP "rx" 12
Receiver Pause is supported
.IP "tx" 12
Transmit Pause is supported
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Configure advertised Pause support depending on if
transmit and receiver pause is supported. If there has been a
change in adverting, trigger a new autoneg. Generally called from
the set_pauseparam .ndo.
